# #7 Java Memory Allocation: Heap and Stack

- JDK, JRE and JVM:

    JVM (Java Virtual Machine) - all java code is built and run on it.

    JDK (Java Development Kit) -  a software development kit (collection) that provides the tools,
     libraries to create, compile, and debug Java applications. It includes the [Java Runtime
     Environment (JRE)](https://www.google.com/search?rlz=1C5CHFA_enAZ1077AZ1077&cs=1&sca_esv=
     e856aeb0adf4cd44&sxsrf=AE3TifMztK2hgjYCidil7M4KLyVRw2CnHg%3A1756780431726&q=Java+Runtime+
     Environment+%28JRE%29&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwicm76MhbmPAxUDR_EDHeP4CuoQxccNegQIBBAB&mstk=AUtExfDyw
     Zvnx8yL5RI3-F8tlrSsC6YbgieCsKhgVCwjh5c59wwXiEfi1Q1e3J40Q4cmWyTxPCJrX8cCBLNonuGdBnn08dJe2hzG
     JIFPpPoew6e8DVNN2KxUilKgG-ZCS2wEBwsrJV4sNEgzZddp9Scd-mWcvx7QjWIkXhku0Dl4rA4zapQ&csui=3)
      (for running Java programs), a Java Compiler(which converts source code to bytecode),
     and Application Programming Interfaces (APIs).

